data.title: Big Dog Ranch Rescue
data.meta_description: Big Dog Ranch Rescue is the largest cage-free, no-kill dog rescue in the United States.
data.text:
Big Dog Ranch Rescue was founded on the idea that every dog deserves to live and most importantly, to live a full and happy life.

We are devoted to creating a healing community for dogs, both big and small, who have been neglected, abandoned, and mistreated.

Our Mission

Our Mission is to Rescue, Rehabilitate and Educate until every dog has a loving and safe place to call home. We believe we can, and we will see an end to dog homelessness and abuse through legislative efforts, hard work and strategic partnerships near and far. We will never give up and we will never back down from the needs of all heartbeats because every life matters.

This 7-year-old gentle giant has a heart as big as his paws. After being found wandering the streets, a sweet woman brought Bubba to Big Dog Ranch Rescue, where he’s now seeking his forever home. Bubba is a calm, lovable companion who’s perfect for seniors looking for looking for a companion to share their golden years.

Cuddle Buddy: Always ready to offer a comforting paw, Bubba is the ultimate snuggle companion

Toy Lover: His love for toys adds a playful touch to his laid-back demeanor

Dog friendly: Enjoys the company og easygoing dogs

Prefers Peace & Quiet: Best suited for a calm environment without children or cats

Make a donation

You can make all the difference

Help support the thousands of animals who come through our gates every year. Big Dog Ranch Rescue is a non-profit. 100% of donations go towards our rescue and our dogs.
